
[1]ammonite

   AM'MONITE, n.[Cornu ammonis, from Jupiter Ammon, whose statues were
   represented with ram's horns.]

   Serpent-stone, or cornu ammonis, a fossil shell, curved into a spiral,
   like a ram's horn; of various sizes, from the smallest grains to three
   feet in diameter. This fossil is found in stratums of limestone and
   clay, and in argillaceous iron ore. It is smooth or ridged; the ridges
   strait, crooked or undulated.
